description: In Addu city, Maldives, India's Foreign Minister S Jaishankar and his Maldivian counterpart Moosa Zameer inaugurated key infrastructure projects. Jaishankar emphasized the importance of the Maldives in India's 'Neighbourhood First' policy. India has invested significantly, with projects aimed at regional development, economic growth, and improved connectivity, reaffirming their strong bilateral relationship.
title: Maldives at heart of 'neighbourhood first' policy: EAM S Jaishankar

description: Samajwadi Party’s Dalit leaders criticized the proposal of sub-categorizing Scheduled Castes, calling it a divisive strategy. Veteran MPs RK Chaudhary and Awadhesh Prasad asserted that the SP, led by Akhilesh Yadav, supports SC/ST unity as envisioned by Ambedkar. This stance aligns with the party's effort to appeal to the weakening BSP vote base.
title: Sub-quota a plot to divide & rule Dalits, allege SP veterans

description: A recent IITM study indicated a significant rise in extreme rainfall events in India by the end of the century due to high carbon dioxide emissions. The Western Ghats and central India are projected to be most affected. Areas with extremely heavy rainfall may increase by 18%, with intensity rising by 58%, impacting socio-economic conditions.
title: 'Extreme rainfall' risks to rise for India: Study

description: Sharad Pawar's convoy was stopped by Maratha activists in Kurduvadi, demanding his support for Maratha reservation. During his rally in Barshi, an activist attempted self-immolation but was stopped by police. Pawar criticized PM Modi for failing to double farmers' incomes and neglecting youth unemployment issues, claiming the economy could suffer as a result.
title: Maratha quota protesters halt Sharad Pawar’s convoy, activist tries self-immolation

description: The 19th crest gate of the 71-year-old Tungabhadra dam in Karnataka malfunctioned, leading to potential flooding risks downstream in Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh. Engineers estimated that 60TMCFT of water needs to be drained before replacing the gate. Officials placed downstream districts on high alert, and Deputy CM DK Shivakumar assessed the situation at the site.
title: Dam gate gives way, puts lakhs in Karnataka, Andhra at flood risk

description: Bengal chief minister Mamata Banerjee contacted Odisha's Mohan Charan Majhi regarding the assault of Bengali-speaking workers in Odisha, labelled as 'Bangladeshis'. Videos showed attacks in Jajpur, Kendrapada, Jagatsinghpur, and Sambalpur. The Odisha government has instructed police to remain vigilant, and a helpline has been launched for affected workers to seek assistance.
title: Bengalis labelled Bangladeshis, attacked in Odisha: Didi to Majhi

description: Four armed men were feared killed in a fratricidal shootout between militants and village guards in Manipur's Tengnoupal district, police reported. A militant from the United Kuki Liberation Front and three village volunteers from the same community reportedly died near Molnom area. Ongoing search operations by central forces have not yet recovered the bodies.
title: Militants, village guards exchange fire, 4 feared killed
Trump falsely accuses Kamala Harris of using AI to show massive crowd at rally

description: Odisha's transport minister recently called for an investigation into helicopter rides taken by V K Pandian, a bureaucrat-turned-politician, between February and September last year. Questions have arisen about the costs and authorization of these rides, as 450 helipads were constructed using government funds. Officials promise a thorough probe into the expenditures and permissions involved.
title: 450 helipads for Naveen aide under scanner

description: Forensic tests confirmed that traces of blood and skin found under the nails of the murdered 31-year-old doctor matched those of Sanjay Roy, the arrested suspect. This evidence was deemed crucial. Roy's policewoman sister disowned him, demanding the harshest punishment. CM Mamata Banerjee urged a fast-track trial, insisting the perpetrator must be hanged.
title: Forensic tests point to suspect’s hand in Kolkata doctor’s rape-murder

description: Heavy rainfall in northern India resulted in the deaths of 31 people across Rajasthan, Himachal Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, and Punjab. Significant incidents included a family in Punjab washed away in their car and multiple drownings in Rajasthan. Officials were working to provide assistance amid widespread damage and disruptions. Rescue operations were ongoing to find missing persons.
title: Rain fury claims 30 lives in 4 northern states; 5 missing

description: Resident doctors at major government hospitals in Delhi decided to indefinitely halt elective services from Monday in protest of the rape and murder of a doctor in Kolkata. They demanded immediate action and increased safety measures for healthcare workers, including enhanced security in hospitals and the implementation of the 'Central Protection Act for Doctors.'
title: Kolkata doctor rape-murder case: Delhi resident doctors to halt elective services indefinitely

description: Congress leaders Mallikarjun Kharge and Rahul Gandhi accused a quid pro quo between Adani Group and Sebi chief Madhabi Buch, calling for a joint parliamentary committee to investigate. Rahul demanded Buch's resignation and questioned the Supreme Court's involvement. AAP demanded PM Modi's resignation, while SP stressed on an impartial Sebi investigation to restore investor confidence.
title: Hindenburg report: Sack Sebi chief, Says Rahul Gandhi; SP, AAP rally behind INDIA ally

description: The BJP claimed that Congress and opposition parties were conspiring to create financial instability in India, rejecting Hindenburg’s accusations against Sebi chairperson Madhabi Buch. Allegations were seen as a plot to destabilize the financial system. BJP stated Hindenburg was in partnership with Congress to disrupt growth, dismissing claims as malicious and baseless.
title: Hindenburg report: Opposition ‘conspiracy’ to destabilise economy, says BJP

description: Police in Meerut registered an FIR against the principal and yoga instructor of a government-run Army Public School after a Class 7 student, who had a retinal problem, went blind following an alleged slap from the yoga instructor. The mother claimed the principal was aware but took no action. The instructor was terminated from service.
title: Student 'loses vision after slap', principal, teacher named in FIR

description: A Dehradun special Pocso court acquitted a 42-year-old man, accused of raping his 15-year-old daughter, after five years in jail. Evidence revealed the girl falsely incriminated him due to his objections to her relationship and school attendance. The court found her allegations instigated by her boyfriend and declared the man innocent last week.
title: Dad freed after 5 years for daughter’s ‘rape’

description: Charubala, the wife of former Manipur MLA Yamthong Haokip, was killed in an explosion in Kangpokpi district. The blast, initially suspected to be a militant attack, might have occurred while she was burning waste in an abandoned compound. Haokip and their daughter were unharmed. Haokip had switched from Congress to BJP before the 2022 assembly polls.
title: IED explosion near home kills ex-MLA’s wife in Manipur
Pelosi says Biden’s letter on 2024 presidential race 'didn't sound like Joe...'

description: Hindenburg Research responded to Madhabi Puri Buch and Dhaval Buch's release, which called their previous report character assassination. Hindenburg highlighted critical questions and admissions, including an email Buch sent in 2018 on behalf of her husband. They questioned Buch's investments through her husband while serving as a SEBI member and noted Buch's connection to a fund linked to Vinod Adani.
title: Madhabi’s response raises new critical questions: Hindenburg Research

description: Sebi chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch and her husband, Dhaval, refuted allegations by Hindenburg regarding their investments linked to Adani stocks. They stressed the investments were made when they were private citizens and were fully disclosed. Sebi backed them, emphasizing adherence to regulations and market integrity. Adani dismissed Hindenburg's claims as manipulative.
title: Buchs, Sebi, Adani, fund deny Hindenburg allegations

description: Jammu & Kashmir’s lieutenant governor Manoj Sinha indicated that assembly elections would soon follow the ongoing delimitation process. Speaking in Srinagar, Sinha noted that the Election Commission had engaged with stakeholders. This will be the first assembly election since 2014, with new seat reservations for Scheduled Tribes.
title: Jammu & Kashmir assembly polls soon, says LG Manoj Sinha

description: The Indian Olympic Association (IOA) president PT Usha has said that IOA-appointed Chief Medical Officer Dr Dinshaw Pardiwala should not be held responsible for the disqualification of Indian wrestler Vinesh Phogat from the women's 50kg final event at the Paris Olympics, and it's the coach and support staff of grappler that should take responsibility.
title: PT Usha defends IOA medical team over Vinesh's disqualification

description: The shootout in Anantnag's upper reaches led to three deaths, including two soldiers and one civilian. The operation continued amidst challenging conditions to trace the terrorists believed to be from Jaish-e-Mohammed. Officials are investigating civilians' presence near the shootout, and preventive measures are in place to ensure safety during local pilgrimages.
title: Civilian dies, toll in Jammu & Kashmir encounter hits 3

description: The Great Indian Kapil Show concluded its first season after 13 episodes and will soon return with season 2. Filming will begin on August 13, with the premiere episode featuring the Bollywood Wives. The last season included appearances from stars like Ranbir Kapoor and international musician Ed Sheeran. The finale featured Sunil Grover and Krushna Abhishek's notable performances.
title: The Great Indian Kapil Show season 2 to go floors from August 13

description: In response to these comments on CBS News’s “Face the Nation,” Vance stated that such views have “no place in the MAGA movement.” He added, “Donald Trump has also criticised this person. Look, I think the guy’s a total loser. I absolutely disavow him. But if you ask me what I care more about, it’s not personal attacks but rather government policies that discriminate based on race. That’s my real concern.” Vance also highlighted the importance of ignoring such attackers, believing that “not feeding the trolls” would cause them to eventually fade away.
title: JD Vance slams white supremacist who mocked his wife...

description: A 7.1 earthquake in southern Japan led to a warning from the Meteorological Agency about possible major quakes. Prime Minister Kishida canceled his Central Asian trip for earthquake preparedness. Experts predict a 70-80% chance of a major quake in the Nankai Trough. Earthquakes with a magnitude greater than 8 are classified as megaquakes.
title: Japan issues its first-ever 'megaquake warning'; know all about 'big one'
Sheikh Hasina's son denies that his mother made resignation statement
Security forces exchange fire with terrorists in J&K's Udhampur

description: Joe Biden, in his first interview post quitting the US presidential race, claimed that Democratic colleagues, influenced by Nancy Pelosi, forced him out to avoid harming their own campaigns. Biden also mentioned that Barack Obama threatened him with the 25th Amendment with Kamala Harris's approval. He raised concerns about a peaceful power transition if Trump loses.
title: Joe Biden name-drops Democrats who pushed him out of presidential race in staged coup

description: Securities and exchange board of India (Sebi) responded to the Hindenburg report, asserting that chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch had made all required disclosures and recused herself in cases of conflict of interest. Sebi clarified the completion of 22 out of 24 investigations into the Adani Group and advised investors to exercise caution before reacting to such reports.
title: Chairperson Madhabi Buch disclosed, recused herself when necessary: Sebi on Hindenburg report
Popular music fades at Trump rallies as Harris hits crescendo

description: Covering just three-square kilometres, the island is home to around 3,700 residents who primarily engage in fishing, rice cultivation, coconut farming, and seaweed harvesting, which is dried and exported to Myanmar. Recently, the island gained attention due to allegations that the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP), led by former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia (who was recently freed), had planned to sell it to the United States for the construction of a military base in exchange for electoral support. However, the US State Department dismissed these claims, affirming its commitment to respecting Bangladesh's sovereignty and promoting democracy through free and fair elections.
title: Sheikh Hasina hints at US role in ouster: What’s significance of St Martin’s Island?

description: Donald Trump wrote on Truth Social: “We were just informed by Microsoft Corporation that one of our many websites was hacked by the Iranian Government - Never a nice thing to do! They were only able to get publicly available information but, nevertheless, they shouldn’t be doing anything of this nature. Iran and others will stop at nothing, because our Government is Weak and Ineffective, but it won’t be for long. What Iran doesn’t realize is that I will make the World a better and safer place, and that’s good for them, also!”
title: Inside Iranian campaign to sabotage Donald Trump's campaign
PM Modi releases 109 new crops, urge experts to engage with farmers

description: The Eiffel Tower was evacuated due to a shirtless man climbing the tower before the Paris Olympics closing ceremony. The man was seen above the first viewing deck, near the Olympic rings. French authorities deployed over 30,000 police officers in Paris, with significant security around the Stade de France. The closing ceremony is scheduled at Stade de France at 9pm.
title: Eiffel Tower evacuated after man climbs up ahead of Paris Olympics closing ceremony

description: Former India batter Wasim Jaffer and former England captain Michael Vaughan are known for their witty interactions on social media, often engaging in friendly banter on a range of topics.
title: Jaffer's savage reply after Vaughan teases him

description: From Shweta Tiwari addressing rumors about Palak Tiwari dating Ibrahim Ali Khan to Sukesh Chandrasekhar gifting Jacqueline Fernandez a yacht on her birthday, today’s top entertainment stories are packed with excitement. Also making headlines are Janhvi Kapoor’s reaction to Shikhar Pahariya's photos, Sobhita Dhulipala’s engagement video, and Shah Rukh Khan’s striking new photoshoot.
title: Read: Top 5 entertainment news of the day
'Phone, WhatsApp working again': Supriya Sule thank authorities

description: Pakistan's first individual Olympic gold medalist, Arshad Nadeem, expressed deep gratitude towards Neeraj Chopra's mother, calling her "my mother too" for praying for both athletes. Nadeem's historic victory in the javelin throw at the Paris Olympics, with a record-breaking 92.97 meters, was celebrated with a hero's welcome in Pakistan. His mother, Raziah Parveen, also expressed affection for Chopra, while Chopra's mother, Saroj Devi, acknowledged Nadeem's gold as a shared victory.
title: 'Neeraj Chopra's mother is my mother': Arshad Nadeem

description: Kamala Harris faced plagiarism accusations from Donald Trump after announcing a policy to eliminate taxes on tips at a rally in Las Vegas. Trump's campaign claimed the idea was originally his. The controversy follows another issue involving Harris' running mate Tim Walz. Despite attacks, recent polls show Harris leading in several swing states.

description: On Minorities' Day, Pakistan's president emphasized promoting interfaith harmony, with recognition of minorities' contributions to nation-building. This came amid violence against minorities in Bangladesh, where Hindu homes and businesses were attacked. Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus condemned the incidents, urging protection for affected families. India continues engaging with Bangladesh's interim government over the issue.
title: Pakistan calls for religious 'tolerance' on Minorities' Day

description: Police formed a Special Investigation Team (SIT) to probe the murder case and arrested a suspect, Sanjay Roy, on Saturday.

description: Security forces intensified their operation in Anantnag district, Jammu and Kashmir, after a civilian succumbed to injuries on Sunday, raising the death toll to three. The encounter in the Ahlan Gagarmandu forest area also saw two soldiers killed on Saturday. Intelligence suggested terrorist presence, triggering the cordon and search. Reinforcements were dispatched, continuing the operation despite challenging terrain.

description: Former Indian cricket captain Sourav Ganguly expressed his support for wrestler Vinesh Phogat, stating she deserved at least a silver medal at the Paris Olympics. Phogat's Olympic campaign ended in controversy when she was disqualified from the final for being 100 grams over the weight limit. Despite a remarkable run in the competition, including a comeback win against reigning champion Yui Susaki, her disqualification has sparked debate, with Ganguly questioning the fairness of the decision.

description: Gunn, a 36-year-old university lecturer from Sydney with a Ph.D. in cultural studies, approached the competition with a creative and unconventional style. Her moves, which she described as entirely original, were a conscious effort to showcase something different and artistic rather than attempting to compete with her peers in terms of athletic prowess. One of her signature moves, the "kangaroo hop," became particularly notorious, drawing both attention and ridicule online.

description: Madhabi Buch, SEBI chairperson, and her husband Dhaval addressed allegations from Hindenburg's research, revealing their 2015 investment made as private citizens. They clarified that the investment decision was influenced by Dhaval's childhood friend, Anil Ahuja, and confirmed no investments in Adani group. They criticized Hindenburg for attacking SEBI's credibility instead of addressing served show cause notice.
title: 'Hindenburg chose character assassination ... ': Sebi chief Madhabi Buch issues detailed rebuttal

description: Medical staff at West Bengal's Bhatar State General Hospital protested after a patient, under the influence, threatened a female doctor with consequences similar to those faced by a trainee medic in a Kolkata hospital if his treatment was delayed. The suspect, Susanta Roy, was arrested. This incident occurred amid public outrage over the brutal rape-murder of a trainee doctor in Kolkata, leading to widespread protests for justice.
title: 'Same treatment as Kolkata doctor': Patient threatens Bengal doctor

description: The political tussle between Congress and BJP escalated after Hindenburg Research's allegations against Sebi chairperson Madhabi Buch. Congress called for immediate action and a JPC probe into the Adani Group investigation, alleging conflicts of interest. BJP dismissed the claims as a conspiracy to destabilize India's financial system by discrediting the regulator.
title: Hindenburg report: Congress demands JPC probe into Sebi's role, BJP calls it conspiracy

description: Akhilesh Yadav targeted BJP following Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge's critique of the Supreme Court's 'creamy layer' judgment, which allows states to create sub-groups within the SC and ST quotas. Yadav argued that reservation should empower neglected communities, not divide them, and slammed BJP for allegedly weakening the reservation fight and betraying the PDA community's trust.

'Stuck for 15 mins': Witness after teen dies due to electrocution

description: Neeraj Chopra, after winning a silver medal in the Paris Olympics, expressed his desire to compete against global javelin stars in India. Despite not being at his physical best, he achieved his season's best throw. Chopra praised fellow athletes Manu Bhaker and PR Sreejesh for their impressive performance and resilience in the Paris Games.

description: NCP (SP) MP Supriya Sule said her phone and WhatsApp had been hacked. She requested people not to message or call her and announced she would file a police complaint. A source close to the leader confirmed that an online police complaint regarding the hacking had been lodged.
title: NCP (SP) MP Supriya Sule claims Phone, WhatsApp hacked

description: China faced extreme heat that caused cars to appear 'pregnant' due to swollen protective wraps. The heat led to the adhesive in the car wraps weakening and expanding, creating a bloated appearance. Despite protective layers, the record-breaking temperatures proved too much, causing significant online buzz and diverse reactions from social media users.
title: Real story behind China’s viral 'pregnant' car videos explained

description: Former Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina accused the United States of influencing her resignation to gain control over Saint Martin Island and the Bay of Bengal. Following student protests and political unrest, Hasina urged citizens against radical manipulation, vowing to return and restore stability. Her son hinted at foreign intelligence involvement in the protests.

description: India celebrated its 78th Independence Day on August 15, marking freedom from British rule. The third edition of the Har Ghar Tiranga campaign will run from August 9 to August 15, 2024, encouraging citizens to display the Indian flag at home. Prime Minister Modi urged people to participate by changing profile pictures and uploading selfies, promoting national pride and patriotism.

description: Kolkata Police volunteer Sanjay Roy was arrested for the rape and murder of a postgraduate doctor at RG Kar Hospital. He was identified through CCTV footage and a torn earphone. The autopsy revealed sexual assault and multiple injuries. The crime occurred early in the morning, with the victim’s body found at 7.30 am.

description: Susan Wojcicki, former YouTube CEO, passed away at 56. Her husband, Dennis Troper, announced the news, and tech leaders like Google’s Sundar Pichai and Apple’s Tim Cook paid tributes. Wojcicki was pivotal in Google's early success and led YouTube's growth. Pichai highlighted her kindness and role in the company’s history.

description: Prince Harry, residing in the United States since 2020, reportedly faced boredom and missed his old friends in the UK. Royal expert Tom Quinn mentioned that Harry's lack of day-to-day activities has created tension with Meghan Markle, who is busy with her projects. Harry misses the UK, adding to his unease.

description: India failed to match its best-ever medal tally of seven from the Tokyo Olympics, ending with six medals in Paris. Despite high hopes with the largest contingent ever, India secured one silver and five bronze. Close misses included disqualification and fourth-place finishes, but improvement in performance was noted across disciplines.

description: The Adani Group denied allegations by Hindenburg Research accusing its connections with Sebi chairperson Madhabi Buch and her husband in an alleged money siphoning scandal. The Adani Group called the claims malicious, emphasizing their transparency and regulatory compliance. Buch and her husband also refuted the allegations, offering complete transparency of their financial documents. description: WWE Raw saw a violent clash when Bronson Reed took on Seth Rollins, resulting in severe injuries for Rollins, including cracked ribs and internal bruising. description: Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore's missions on the ISS were extended following issues with the Boeing Starliner spacecraft. Due to a helium leak, their return, initially planned for June 2024, is now uncertain. Nasa has indicated an alternative return plan using SpaceX's Crew Dragon capsule, potentially in February 2025, posing challenges for Boeing.

description: A US judge ruled Google a monopolist for its search dominance. Sundar Pichai sold Google shares, while Cisco and Dell announced layoffs. India's TRAI cracked down on spam calls, and the CBI warned of a 'WhatsApp-CBI scam' and other top tech news of the week.

description: A researcher from the University of Edinburgh uncovered the earliest lunisolar calendar at Göbekli Tepe, an ancient site in Turkey. Martin Sweatman linked markings on a pillar to a comet impact 13,000 years ago, suggesting ancient people recorded this event. The discovery hints at advanced astronomical understanding of that time.

description: K Natwar Singh, former Congress leader and diplomat, passed away at 93 after a prolonged illness. Known for roles in diplomacy and politics, Singh held key positions including external affairs minister. Implicated in the 2005 Iraqi oil scam, he resigned amidst controversy. Singh authored several books, and received the Padma Bhushan in 1984.

description: Former Delhi Deputy CM Manish Sisodia celebrated his second day of release by sharing moments with his children, calling them 'God'. After stepping out of Tihar jail, he credited his release to the Constitution and 'Truth'. Sisodia expressed confidence that Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal would also be freed soon. description: Madhabi Puri Buch, SEBI chairperson, and her husband, Dhaval Buch, denied allegations by Hindenburg Research regarding their involvement in offshore entities tied to the Adani Group scandal. description: Bengaluru police arrested a Third wave Coffee employee for hiding a phone in a women's restroom dustbin to secretly record videos. While not directly causing crashes, these incidents could lead to serious complications.

description: In the early hours of May 6, 2023, two men detonated explosives in an ATM at a German bank in Bad Homburg, making off with ₹165,000. description: Olympic medalist Yogeshwar Dutt shared optimism about Vinesh Phogat’s appeal on her disqualification from the Paris Olympics. The Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) extended the decision deadline to August 13, 2024. Phogat was disqualified for a slight weight breach. Her family and supporters eagerly await the verdict, hoping it might add another medal to India’s tally.
title: 'Umeed karte hai desh ke khate me medal jude': Dutt on Vinesh's appeal
